<dl id="n05021a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05021a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05021a"> 21(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> eclipse (stakes)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The miracles of the earthquake and the <mark>eclipse</mark> at the Crucifixion will be discussed in our <font color="green">[next]</font> chapter on the Resurrection. Dr. Farrar minimises the darkness over &ldquo;all the earth&rdquo; into &ldquo;a local gloom which hung densely over the guilty city and its immediate neighbourhood.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Crucifixion] 201</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
